# Include Directory - MDS-01 Dehumidifier

This directory contains project header files.

## Current Headers

### pins.h
Defines all GPIO pin assignments for the ESP32-S3. Edit this file if you need to change hardware connections.

**Pin Definitions:**
| Define | GPIO | Function |
|--------|------|----------|
| NEOPIXEL_PIN | 14 | WS2812B RGB LED strip |
| CLOCK | 36 | LCD SPI Clock |
| DATA | 35 | LCD SPI Data (MOSI) |
| CS | 21 | LCD Chip Select |
| DC | 47 | LCD Data/Command |
| RESET | 13 | LCD Reset |
| DHT_PIN | 12 | DHT22 Sensor Data |
| EN_A | 5 | Rotary Encoder A |
| EN_B | 4 | Rotary Encoder B |
| EN_BTN | 1 | Rotary Encoder Button |
| BUZZER | 48 | Piezo Buzzer |
| RELAY_1 | 15 | Fan Relay Control |
| RELAY_2 | 16 | Heater Relay Control |

## Adding New Headers

To add a new header file:
1. Create your `.h` file in this directory
2. Include it in your source files:

```cpp
#include "your_header.h"
```

## Standard Include Pattern

```cpp
// In src/main.cpp
#include <Arduino.h>       // System headers use angle brackets
#include <U8g2lib.h>       // Library headers use angle brackets
#include "pins.h"          // Project headers use quotes
#include "your_header.h"   // Your custom headers
```

## Notes
- Header guards are recommended to prevent multiple inclusion
- Keep pin definitions in `pins.h` for easy hardware reconfiguration
- Use `#define` for compile-time constants
